<title>USA: Randgold launches ADR.</title>
<headline>Randgold launches ADR.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-03-13</dateline>
<text>
<p>South African gold mining company Randgold &amp; Exploration Co Ltd has begun to trade its American Depositary Receipts (ADRs) on the Nasdaq National Market, the exchange said on Thursday.</p>
<p>The Bank of New York is its depositary bank. The ADR ratio, which represents the number of ADRs per underlying share, is one to one.</p>
<p>Randgold is the sixth South African ADR to list on the Nasdaq in the past six months, the exchange said in a statement.</p>
<p>The company is one of the top 10 gold producers in the world.</p>
<p>The shares began to trade on Monday. They closed on Wednesday at eight.</p>
<p>((--Ian Simpson, Wall Street desk, (212) 859-1879))</p>
